Here, FTA finds that the weight of the documentary evidence in 
its records, including responses of grantees to complaints by 
private operators, protests from labor unions representing 
transit workers, and documented failures of specific 
privatization programs to realize cost savings or improvements 
in service quality, strongly indicates that the policy has 
